April 11 (Reuters) - Bitcoin dropped 5.3% to $39,881.02 at on Monday, down $2,231.58 from its previous close. Bitcoin, the world's biggest and best-known cryptocurrency, is down 17.3% from the year's high of $48,234 on March 28. Ether , the coin linked to the ethereum blockchain network, dipped 6.58 % to $2,991.51 on Monday, losing $210.86 from its previous close. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.